race.comment: FULMEN FILOU (2) brings a last start win delivered easily over 2200m at Grafton. Has been threatening and keeps the handy 2kg claim. Can go on with it now. EJECT (7) comes out of the same race and didn't have much luck early. His near miss at Gunnedah prior over this distance stacks up. Nestor goes on and will be keen to settle the gelding closer in the run. FINAL IMPACT (3) found one much too good as a 3.0F at Dubbo but covered the others. He was bumped at the start and an each-way pop in this lineup. SONDER (4) should secure a soft run from an inside barrier. He was well in the market at Grafton last time but was slow away. In the mix,
